Aleutian Islands Akutan Volcano Granular Sonification

This project is a data sonification engine that transforms seismic data from the Akutan Volcanos of the Aleutian Islands (1997–2017) into immersive audio using C++ and the Synthesis ToolKit (STK). 
This project involves mapping seismic parameters including magnitude, depth, and frequency to granular synthesis parameters.
the engine creates a two minute sonification representing two decades of volcanic activity.

The dataset is provided by Hannah Mark, Lamont Assistant Research Professor in Marine & Polar Geophysics.

This project was developed as part of MUS 410 at the University of Oregon.

Dependencies
This project requires the Synthesis ToolKit (STK). Ensure it is installed on your system:

macOS (Homebrew): brew install stk

Linux (Ubuntu/Debian): sudo apt-get install libstk0-dev

Setup & Compilation
1. Directory Structure
Ensure your project folder is organized as follows:

root/
├── audio_output/
│   └── akutan_sonification.wav
├── data/
│   ├── cleaned/
│   │   └── akutan_cleaned.csv
│   └── raw/
│       └── akutan_raw.csv
├── IR/
│   └── fm-ir1.wav
└── src/
    ├── akutan_render.cpp
    └── akutan-clean.py

2. Compilation
Compile the project using g++ with the necessary include and library paths.

Bash
g++ -std=c++17 -I/opt/homebrew/include/stk -L/opt/homebrew/lib akutan_render.cpp -lstk -o sonify

3. Execution
Run the compiled binary from the project root:

Bash
./sonify
The engine will process akutan_cleaned.csv and generate the final sonification in the audio_output/ folder.